<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF44719FF5BF8F8FD98FE59" blockId="48.[212,1135,1822,1845]" lastBlockId="49.[242,1475,266,671]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB26118DFFF44719FF5BF8F8FD98FE59" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">
<treatmentCitation id="0A9710B2FFF44718FF5BF8F8FDEEF89F" author="PERROUD B. P." box="[212,548,1822,1845]" page="147" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" year="1865">
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF44718FF5BF8F8FDEEF89F" authority="Perroud, 1865: 147" authorityName="Perroud" authorityPageNumber="147" authorityYear="1865" box="[212,548,1822,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF44718FF5BF8F8FEA2F89E" box="[212,360,1824,1845]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">Anomalodermus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA74B52FFF44718FEE2F8C6FDEEF89F" author="PERROUD B. P." box="[365,548,1822,1845]" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" pagination="179 - 202" refId="ref87927" refString="Revue FranCaise d'Entomologie 11 (4): 179 - 202. WATERHOUSE C. O. 1877. - Descriptions of twenty new species of Coleoptera PERROUD B. P. 1865. - in PERROUD B. P. &amp; MONTROUZIER X. 1865 (see from various localities. Transactions of the Entomological Society of next). London: 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1865">Perroud, 1865: 147</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
(
<typeStatus id="548D8801FFF44718FDBFF8C7FD91F89F" box="[560,603,1823,1844]" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF44718FD24F8F8FC60F89E" authority="Perroud" authorityName="Perroud" box="[683,938,1823,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosocostatus">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF44718FD24F8F8FC99F89E" box="[683,851,1824,1845]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">A. flexuosocostatus</emphasis>
Perroud
</taxonomicName>
). — 
<treatmentCitation id="0A9710B2FFF44718FC42F8C6FBA1F89F" author="HELLER K. M." box="[973,1131,1822,1844]" page="312" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" year="1916">
<bibRefCitation id="EFA74B52FFF44718FC42F8C6FBA1F89F" author="HELLER K. M." box="[973,1131,1822,1844]" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" pagination="10" refId="ref85064" refString="59: 43 - 98. HELLER K. M. 1916. - Die Kafer von Neu-Caledonien und den benachbarten DEJEAN P. F. M. A. 1821. - Catalogue de la collection de Coleopteres de M. Inselgruppen. In Sarasin &amp; Roux (eds) Nova Caledonia. A. Zoologie 2 (3): le Baron Dejean. Paris, Crevot. 8 + 136 + 2 pp. 229 - 365, pl. 10, 11." type="book chapter" year="1916">Heller 1916: 312</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
. DESCRIPTION. — Adelognathous; eyes distinctly transverse, flat, coarse; rostrum on midline raised to a blunt ridge; scrobes directed towards upper part of eyes; scape reaching or slightly passing hind margin of eyes, directed towards upper part of eyes, in lateral view bent upwards; club segment 1 much shorter than remainder of club; ocular lobes moderately developed, with short or longish cilia; pronotum convex, disc neither flattened nor depressed; scutellum very small or concealed; elytra lacking humeral callus; odd interstriae subcostiform or tuberculate; hind tibiae with narrow glabrous or sparsely pilose corbel plate, with small mucro; claws free, divergent; metepisternum concealed except for anterior tip. Flightless.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF54719FE9FFE25FB23FDF1" blockId="49.[242,1475,266,671]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">Male: tegmen with parameral lobes. Aedeagus extending into metathoracic cavity; apodemes not or slightly longer than aedeagal body; internal sac not extended cepahalad from base of aedeagal body or reaching to half the length of apodemes, with proximally articulated basal sclerite, this robust and cylindrical, or flagelliform.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6528FFF54719FE9FFDBDFE64FD34" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF54719FE9FFDBDFE64FD34" blockId="49.[242,1475,266,671]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">
Female: ovipositor of the 
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF54719FDADFDBDFD2BFDD7" box="[546,737,613,636]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">Catoptes-Leptopius</emphasis>
group of genera with relatively broad hemisternites, long styli, short vagina and bursa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6528FFF54719FF7DFD15FD1EFD4E" box="[242,724,717,741]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF54719FF7DFD15FD1EFD4E" blockId="49.[242,724,717,741]" box="[242,724,717,741]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">
DISTRIBUTION. — 
<collectingCountry id="F3217633FFF54719FE4CFD15FDA2FD4E" box="[451,616,717,741]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, endemic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6528FFF54719FF7DFCCAFDDAFCE6" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF54719FF7DFCCAFDDAFCE6" blockId="49.[242,1474,786,845]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">ETYMOLOGY. — A latinised compound derived from the Greek ‘anomalós’ meaning aberrant, unusual, and ‘derma’ for skin or body wrapping.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6528FFF54719FF7DFCA2FE78FBB6" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF54719FF7DFCA2FE78FBB6" blockId="49.[242,1474,890,1053]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">
REMARKS. — 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF54719FE0AFCA3FDE0FC39" box="[389,554,891,914]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF54719FE0AFCA3FDE0FC39" box="[389,554,891,914]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">Anomalodermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in appearance much like the Australian 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF54719FC64FCA3FB05FC39" authority="Schoenherr" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1840" box="[1003,1231,890,914]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Amisallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF54719FC64FCA3FB87FC39" box="[1003,1101,891,914]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">Amisallus</emphasis>
Schoenherr
</taxonomicName>
, the latter having open corbels on hind tibiae, scrobes and scape directed towards the lower part of eyes, and, in lateral view, a downwards curved scape. Three spectacularly different species are present, which ought to suggest that a number of other species remain to be discovered. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA74B52FFF54719FD8FFC3AFD45FC51" author="HELLER K. M." box="[512,655,994,1018]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" pagination="10" refId="ref85064" refString="59: 43 - 98. HELLER K. M. 1916. - Die Kafer von Neu-Caledonien und den benachbarten DEJEAN P. F. M. A. 1821. - Catalogue de la collection de Coleopteres de M. Inselgruppen. In Sarasin &amp; Roux (eds) Nova Caledonia. A. Zoologie 2 (3): le Baron Dejean. Paris, Crevot. 8 + 136 + 2 pp. 229 - 365, pl. 10, 11." type="book chapter" year="1916">Heller (1916)</bibRefCitation>
provided a key to the species but none of the four keyed out by him belong in 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF54719FE82FBDEFE78FBB6" box="[269,434,1030,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF54719FE82FBDEFE78FBB6" box="[269,434,1030,1053]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">Anomalodermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6528FFF54719FD1DFB92FAA1FA99" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" type="key">
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF54719FD1DFB92FBE8FBCA" blockId="49.[658,1058,1098,1121]" box="[658,1058,1098,1121]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">
KEY TO SPECIES OF 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF54719FCEEFB92FBE8FBCA" box="[865,1058,1098,1121]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF54719FCEEFB92FBE8FBCA" box="[865,1058,1098,1121]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">ANOMALODERMUS</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF54719FEC6FB57FAA1FA99" blockId="49.[329,1388,1167,1330]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">
1. Rostrum, pronotum and elytra with long erect setae besides a pile of short clavate pilosity. Scrobes, in front of eyes, with sharp, cariniform lower edge. Elytra with low tubercles only. 
<quantity id="4CCE9B46FFF54719FB64FB6AFAA2FB62" box="[1259,1384,1202,1226]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8499999999999996" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" unit="mm" value="3.8499999999999996" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.8">3.8-3.9 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F3217633FFF54719FEC6FB0DFE26FB46" box="[329,492,1237,1261]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
..................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF54719FB73FB0DFAA1FB47" authorityName="Kuschel" authorityYear="2008" box="[1276,1387,1237,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incrustatus">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF54719FB73FB0DFAA1FB47" box="[1276,1387,1237,1260]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">incrustatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
— Rostrum, pronotum and elytra with short, recumbent or raised clavate setae only. Scrobes, in front of eyes, with blunt, not cariniform edge. Elytra with large tubercles ....................................................... 2
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6528FFF54719FEC6FA9DFAA1FA43" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFF54719FEC6FA9DFAA1FA43" blockId="49.[329,1388,1349,1512]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">
2. Interstria 3 at base raised to a low ridge, ridge not advancing forward onto pronotum. Elytra beyond middle with one tubercle on interstria 3. 5.8-8.0 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="F3217633FFF54719FC55FAB0FBB7FAD4" box="[986,1149,1383,1407]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
........... 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF54719FB44FAB1FAA1FA2B" box="[1227,1387,1385,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosocostatus">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF54719FB44FAB1FAA1FA2B" box="[1227,1387,1385,1408]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">flexuosocostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
— Interstria 3 at base raised to a large bulky tubercle, this advancing forwatd onto pronotum. Elytra beyond middle with two tubercles each, one on interstria 3, the other on 5. 6.0-7.0 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="F3217633FFF54719FAB5FA75FE7FFA4C" name="New Caledonia" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
.................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D20FFF54719FA97FA09FAA1FA43" authorityName="Kuschel" authorityYear="2008" box="[1304,1387,1489,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proclivis">
<emphasis id="B942EAB1FFF54719FA97FA09FAA1FA43" box="[1304,1387,1489,1512]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">proclivis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
